-- Aquatech Wins Wastewater Facility Contract for U.S. Power Plant
-- B y   R a n d a l l   H a c k l e y
-- 2012-07-23T14:13:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-23/aquatech-wins-wastewater-facility-contract-for-u-s-power-plant.html
Aquatech International Corp., a
water purification technology provider, won a contract in
 Mississippi  for an integrated gasification combined-cycle power
plant that emits no processed wastewater in the environment.  No terms were disclosed for the water treatment and
wastewater treatment facilities for the power plant owned by
Mississippi Power Co. near De Kalb, the Canonsburg,
Pennsylvania-based company said. Aquatech said in a statement
today that the zero liquid discharge system to be used at the
site is the “most environmentally friendly option for supplying
water to the Kemper County” facility.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Randall Hackley in Zurich at 
